parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front spring perch can cause the front suspension to collapse, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The front spring perch rusts out
the vehicle drops to the ground
and the vehicle may lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deterioration of the engine wiring harness can cause electrical shorts, leading to loss of power, engine stalling, and potentially, fires. This can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: brittle or broken insulation on individual wires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deterioration of the electrical wiring harness can cause sudden loss of engine and electrical functions, leading to stalling or failure of critical systems, which can increase the risk of accidents, fires, or leave the driver stranded.
